'''Ayoub El Kaabi''' ([[Berber languages]]: ⴰⵢⵓⴱ ⴻⵍ ⴽⴰⴰⴱⵉ, {{langx|ar|أَيُّوب الْكَعْبِيّ}}; born 25 June 1993) is a Moroccan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Super League Greece]] club [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hatayspor yeni forvetini buldu: Ayoub El Kaabi|url=https://www.sozcu.com.tr/spor/futbol/hatayspor-yeni-forvetini-buldu-ayoub-el-kaabi-6604846/|access-date=21 August 2021|website=Sozcu|language=tr|archive-date=9 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240509213740/https://www.sozcu.com.tr/hatayspor-yeni-forvetini-buldu-ayoub-el-kaabi-wp6604846|url-status=live}}</ref>

Born in Casablanca, El Kaabi left school at the age of 15 and worked as a carpenter, before he started his professional career playing for [[Racing de Casablanca]]. After a career at various teams and a short spell at [[Al Sadd SC|Al Sadd]], he signed for Greek club Olympiacos.

While with Olympiacos, El Kaabi finished as the top scorer of both the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League]], with eleven goals, and the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League]], with seven goals in just eight appearances.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kabbour |first=Abderrahim |date=23 May 2025 |title=Morocco's Ayoub El Kaabi Shines as Europa League Joint-Top Scorer |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2025/05/202868/moroccos-ayoub-el-kaabi-shines-as-europa-league-joint-top-scorer/ |access-date=25 May 2025 |website=Morocco World News}}</ref> With Olympiacos, he has won a [[UEFA Conference League|Conference League]], [[2024–25 Super League Greece|Super League]], and [[2024–25 Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]] title.

A full international for Morocco since 2018, El Kaabi represented the nation at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], three [[Africa Cup of Nations]] tournaments, two [[African Nations Championship]] tournaments and won [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations|2025 African Cup of Nations]]. He was the top goalscorer of the [[2018 African Nations Championship]], with a record nine goals.<ref name="NFT">{{cite web|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/69930/Ayoub_El_Kaabi.html|title=El Kaabi, Ayoub|website=National Football Teams|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=18 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118011347/http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/69930/Ayoub_El_Kaabi.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=5 February 2018 |title=CHAN 2018 : Ayoub El Kaabi élu meilleur joueur |trans-title=CHAN 2018: Ayoub El Kaabi named best player |url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/chan-2018-ayoub-el-kaabi-elu-meilleur-joueur |access-date=25 April 2025 |website=Afrik Foot|language=fr}}</ref>

==Early life==
Ayoub El Kaabi was born and raised in the disadvantaged neighborhood of Derb Milla in [[Casablanca]].<ref name="MC">{{Cite web |date=2018-04-01 |title=Al-Kaabi: There is no place for decency among the "lions"... and I sang "Haha, my cousin." |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%84%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B4%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%AF-419194.html |access-date=2024-02-19 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=19 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240219071756/https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%84%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B4%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%AF-419194.html |url-status=live }}</ref> His family is from [[Zagora, Morocco|Zagora]] in southern Morocco, but moved to the region of [[Mediouna, Morocco|Mediouna]] near Casablanca. The El Kaabi family went through difficult times in the 1990s.<ref name="MC" /> As a result, El Kaabi left school at the age of 15 and worked at a [[workshop|shop]] in the Mediouna district as an apprentice [[Carpentry|carpenter]].<ref name="MC" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-06-25 |title=أيوب الكعبي.. من نجّار مبتدئ إلى لاعب أساسي في كأس العالم |trans-title=Ayoub El Kaabi: From an apprentice carpenter to a key player in the World Cup. |url=https://arabi21.com/story/1104209/%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%86%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%AA%D8%AF%D8%A6-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D8%A3%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85 |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=عربي21 |language=ar}}</ref> As he explained in an interview with the Moroccan press: "I was born into a modest family. To support myself, I had to learn a trade. That's how I got into carpentry."

Like nearly all young people in the city, El Kaabi was interested in [[association football|football]] from a young age and he played football with his neighborhood friends. Realising his unique talent, his entourage advised him to join a club in the Hay Khadija district. After only a few months, he came to the attention of the [[Scout (association football)|scouts]] of [[Racing de Casablanca]] who were impressed with his technical ability and physical presence.<ref name="MC" /> El Kaabi gave up carpentry to devote himself to football and signed his first professional contract at the age of 21 with Racing Club in 2014.<ref name="MC" />

==Club career==
===Racing de Casablanca===
After playing for CH Khadija as a youth player, El Kaabi joined [[Racing de Casablanca]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.flashscore.co.uk/news/football-europa-conference-league-ayoub-el-kaabi-the-casablanca-carpenter-turned-olympiacos-hero/ryiLaxjB/|title=Ayoub El Kaabi: The Casablanca carpenter turned Olympiacos hero|publisher=FlashScore|date=29 May 2025|access-date=14 January 2026}}</ref> Prior to breaking into the first team at Racing de Casablanca, El Kaabi played for amateur sides Ettifaq Lalla Meryem and Club Chaâb de Casablanca on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ahdath.info/358302|title=أيوب الكعبي: عندما كان النجم لاعبا في اتفاق للا مريم (صور)|publisher=Al Ahdath Al Maghribia|date=24 January 2018|access-date=14 January 2026|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultrasawt.com/%D8%AD%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%88%D9%84%D9%87-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B4%D8%A9-%D9%86%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%81/%D8%BA%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AB-%D8%AA%D9%81%D9%86%D9%83%D8%AC%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9|title=حكاية أيوب الكعبي وتحوله من ورشة نجارة إلى لاعب محترف|publisher=Ultrasawt|date=26 February 2024|access-date=14 January 2026|language=ar}}</ref> El Kaabi initially began his career at Racing de Casablanca as a left-back due to his speed and stamina, the club switched him to defensive midfielder, and then to forward after Racing de Casablanca's manager saw his great finishing ability. He was credited with helping the club gain promotion to the [[Botola Pro]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ayoub El Kaabi |url=https://areq.net/m/%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8_%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A.html |access-date=24 December 2021 |website=areq.net |archive-date=24 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211224111555/https://areq.net/m/%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8_%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

===RS Berkane===
Ayoub El Kaabi joined [[RS Berkane]] on transfer from Racing during summer 2017 as top scorer in the [[Botola 2]] during the 2016–17 season with 25 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transfert. Officiel: la RSB s'offre la vedette de la D2 et enflamme le Mercato |trans-title=Transfer. Official: RSB signs the star of the second division and ignites the transfer market. |url=https://sport.le360.ma/botola-pro/transfert-officiel-la-rsb-soffre-la-vedette-de-la-d2-et-enflamme-le-mercato-35866/ |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=Le 360 Sport Français |language=fr}}</ref> El Kaabi won the [[2018 Moroccan Throne Cup]] when Berkane defeated [[Wydad de Fès]] in the final on penalties.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Morocco 2017/18|url=https://www.rsssf.org/tablesm/maro2018.html|access-date=10 January 2022|website=[[RSSSF]]|archive-date=13 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220913101710/https://www.rsssf.org/tablesm/maro2018.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Hebei China Fortune===
In 2018, El Kaabi was purchased by [[Hebei China Fortune]] for a transfer fee of €6.5 million.<ref>{{cite news|language=en|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/chinese-club-force-zamalek-to-withdraw-interest-in-morocco/1894ntw5mxnrx102le6akgak37|title=Chinese Club Forced Zamalek to withdraw interest from Morocco striker Ayoub El-Kaabi|date=11 July 2018|access-date=11 July 2018|archive-date=11 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711143843/http://www.goal.com/en/news/chinese-club-force-zamalek-to-withdraw-interest-in-morocco/1894ntw5mxnrx102le6akgak37|url-status=live}}</ref>
[[File:阿尤布·艾尔·卡比.png|alt=|thumb|El Kaabi playing for [[Hebei F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]]|100px|right]]

On 2 August, El Kaabi scored his first goal for the club against [[Beijing Guoan]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=El Kaabi fires in superb volley for Hebei|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en/football/video/el-kaabi-fires-in-superb-volley-for-hebei/943494|access-date=1 January 2022|website=beIN SPORTS|language=en|archive-date=1 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220101195735/https://www.beinsports.com/en/football/video/el-kaabi-fires-in-superb-volley-for-hebei/943494|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Wydad===
In July 2019, El Kaabi joined Wydad AC.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 July 2019 |title=Officiel: Ayoub El Kaabi jouera avec le WAC |trans-title=Official: Ayoub El Kaabi will play with WAC. |url=https://www.lesiteinfo.com/sport/ayoub-el-kaabi-jouera-avec-le-wac/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728174854/https://www.lesiteinfo.com/sport/ayoub-el-kaabi-jouera-avec-le-wac/ |archive-date=28 July 2019 |access-date=20 September 2021 |website=Le Site Info |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Botola: Ayoub El Kaabi a signé au Wydad |trans-title=Botola: Ayoub El Kaabi has signed with Wydad. |url=http://m.2m.ma/fr/news/en-attendant-lannonce-officielle-ayoub-el-kaabi-a-signe-au-wydad-20200924/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210921011724/https://m.2m.ma/fr/news/en-attendant-lannonce-officielle-ayoub-el-kaabi-a-signe-au-wydad-20200924/ |archive-date=21 September 2021 |access-date=20 September 2021 |website=2M |language=fr}}</ref> He took part in the qualifying stages of the [[2019–20 CAF Champions League]] before signing to the Turkish side [[Hatayspor]]. During the competition El Kaabi managed to score a hat-trick against [[Atlético Petróleos de Luanda]] marking his final match for [[Wydad]].<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=CAF-Confedération Africaine du Football|title=El Kaabi hat-trick earns Wydad first group stage win {{!}} Total CAF Champions League 2020/21|url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-caf-champions-league/news/el-kaabi-hat-trick-earns-wydad-first-group-stage-win|access-date=24 December 2021|website=CAFOnline.com|language=en|archive-date=24 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211224194101/https://www.cafonline.com/total-caf-champions-league/news/el-kaabi-hat-trick-earns-wydad-first-group-stage-win|url-status=live}}</ref> He finished as the top scorer of the Botola in the 2020–21 season with 18 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Vidéo. Botola Pro D1 Inwi: El Kaabi, officiellement meilleur buteur |trans-title=Video. Botola Pro D1 Inwi: El Kaabi, officially the top scorer. |url=https://m.le360.ma/sport//botola-pro-1/video-botola-pro-d1-inwi-el-kaabi-officiellement-meilleur-buteur-87332 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210920212349/https://m.le360.ma/sport//botola-pro-1/video-botola-pro-d1-inwi-el-kaabi-officiellement-meilleur-buteur-87332 |archive-date=20 September 2021 |access-date=20 September 2021 |website=Le360 Sport |language=fr}}</ref>

===Hatayspor===
In 2021, El Kaabi signed a two-year contract until June 2023 with Hatayspor,<ref>{{Cite web|date=21 August 2021|title=Ayoub El Kaabi moved to Hatayspor club until June 2023|url=https://en.hespress.com/25199-ayoub-el-kaabi-moved-to-hatayspor-club-until-june-2023.html|access-date=6 January 2022|website=HESPRESS English - Morocco's leading digital media|language=en-US|archive-date=6 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220106203548/https://en.hespress.com/25199-ayoub-el-kaabi-moved-to-hatayspor-club-until-june-2023.html|url-status=live}}</ref> after having made the heyday of Wydad in Casablanca.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=21 August 2021|title=Ayoub El Kaabi joins Turkish club Hatayspor|url=https://moroccolatestnews.com/ayoub-el-kaabi-joins-turkish-club-hatayspor/|access-date=6 January 2022|website=Morocco Latest News|language=en-US|archive-date=6 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220106203548/https://moroccolatestnews.com/ayoub-el-kaabi-joins-turkish-club-hatayspor/|url-status=usurped}}</ref>

On 23 August 2021, El Kaabi made his debut for the team, after being substituted in 76th minute for [[Mame Diouf]] against [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]], the game ended in a 2–1 loss. On 28 August he scored his first goal with the team after a 5–0 victory against [[Alanyaspor]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=أول هدف للكعبي في الدوري التركي |trans-title=El Kaabi's first goal in the Turkish league. |url=https://snrtnews.com/article/%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84-%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%81-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303185559/https://snrtnews.com/article/%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84-%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%81-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A |archive-date=3 March 2022 |access-date=3 March 2022 |website=SNRTnews |language=ar}}</ref> On 27 February 2022, El Kaabi scored his first hat-trick for the club in a 5–2 win against [[Yeni Malatyaspor]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=El Kaabi'den hat-trick... Atakaş Hatayspor 5-2 Öznur Kablo Yeni Malatyspor (Maç sonucu) |trans-title=A hat-trick from El Kaabi... Atakaş Hatayspor 5-2 Öznur Kablo Yeni Malatyspor (Match result). |url=https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/hatayspor-malatyaspor-u-5-golle-gecti-621b90be4ccc9c1be02a9194 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227150117/https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/hatayspor-malatyaspor-u-5-golle-gecti-621b90be4ccc9c1be02a9194 |archive-date=27 February 2022 |access-date=27 February 2022 |website=NTVSpor.net |language=tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=El Kaabi coştu, Hatayspor uçtu {{!}} Mackolik.com |url=https://www.mackolik.com/futbol/haber/el-kaabi-costu-hatayspor-uctu/dfr94lb253sk1y0h7kf3zwrl5 |access-date=27 February 2022 |website=www.mackolik.com |archive-date=27 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227171904/https://www.mackolik.com/futbol/haber/el-kaabi-costu-hatayspor-uctu/dfr94lb253sk1y0h7kf3zwrl5 |url-status=live }}</ref> Due to the [[2023 Turkey–Syria earthquake]], the club withdrew from the league after the club's quarters in [[Antakya]] collapsed.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Son Dakika: Hatayspor ligden çekildi! TFF Başkanı Mehmet Büyükekşi açıkladı |trans-title=Breaking News: Hatayspor withdraws from the league! TFF President Mehmet Büyükekşi announced. |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/son-dakika-hatayspor-ligden-cekildi-tff-baskani-mehmet-buyukeksi-acikladi-42217665 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230209185429/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/son-dakika-hatayspor-ligden-cekildi-tff-baskani-mehmet-buyukeksi-acikladi-42217665 |archive-date=9 February 2023 |access-date=2 March 2023 |website=www.hurriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref> This forced El Kaabi to search for another club.

===Al Sadd===
On 1 March 2023, Qatari club [[Al Sadd SC]] reached an agreement with El Kaabi to join the club until the end of the current season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 March 2023 |title=السد القطري يعلن التعاقد مع أيوب الكعبي |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8-1131125.html |access-date=2 March 2023 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=1 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230301172338/https://www.hespress.com/%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b3%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%82%d8%b7%d8%b1%d9%8a-%d9%8a%d8%b9%d9%84%d9%86-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%aa%d8%b9%d8%a7%d9%82%d8%af-%d9%85%d8%b9-%d8%a3%d9%8a%d9%88%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%83%d8%b9%d8%a8-1131125.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Eltayeb |first=Mohamed |date=2 March 2023 |title=Al Sadd and Umm Salal FC find replacements for star footballers ahead of Amir Cup |url=https://dohanews.co/al-sadd-and-umm-salal-fc-find-replacements-for-star-footballers-ahead-of-amir-cup/ |access-date=2 March 2023 |website=Doha News {{!}} Qatar |language=en-US |archive-date=2 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230302112549/https://dohanews.co/al-sadd-and-umm-salal-fc-find-replacements-for-star-footballers-ahead-of-amir-cup/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1 March 2023 |title=Le Marocain Ayoub El Kaabi rejoint le Qatar |trans-title=Moroccan Ayoub El Kaabi joins Qatar. |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20230301-le-marocain-ayoub-el-kaabi-rejoint-le-qatar |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230301181210/https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20230301-le-marocain-ayoub-el-kaabi-rejoint-le-qatar |archive-date=1 March 2023 |access-date=2 March 2023 |website=RFI |language=fr}}</ref> On 3 March, he came on in the 81st minute in place of [[Akram Afif]] and played his first match against [[Al-Sailiya SC]]. On 7 March 2023, El Kaabi scored his first goal in his second appearance for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 March 2023 |title=الكعبي يفتتح التهديف مع نادي السد القطري |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%AA%D8%AA%D8%AD-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%81-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B7-1134798.html |access-date=8 March 2023 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=8 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230308054834/https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%AA%D8%AA%D8%AD-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%81-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B7-1134798.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In the league, he received his first start on 17 March against [[Al-Shamal SC]].

El Kaabi ended the season as third in the championship and finalist in the Qatar Cup played on 6 April 2023 against [[Al-Duhail SC]] in [[Doha]].

===Olympiacos===
On 6 August 2023, it was announced that El Kaabi would join [[Super League Greece|Greek]] side [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 August 2023 |title=رسميا .. نادي أولمبياكوس يرحب بالكعبي |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%88%D8%B3-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%AD%D8%A8-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-1213066.html |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=7 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230807221005/https://www.hespress.com/%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%88%D8%B3-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%AD%D8%A8-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-1213066.html |url-status=live }}</ref> El Kaabi made his debut four days later against [[K.R.C. Genk]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round]]. He managed to score a brace in his fourth appearance for the team in a 3–1 victory against [[FK Čukarički]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 August 2023 |title=A compelling Legend against Čukarički |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2023/08/25/a-compelling-legend-against-cukaricki/ |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902150634/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2023/08/25/a-compelling-legend-against-cukaricki/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Olympiakos 3-1 Cukaricki Belgrade (24 Aug, 2023) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/685881 |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=ESPN |language=en |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902150633/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/685881 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 21 September 2023, El Kaabi scored a brace against [[SC Freiburg]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League#Group stage|Europa League group stage]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2023 |title=They didn't make it at the opening phase of the group stage |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2023/09/22/they-didn-t-make-it-at-the-opening-phase-of-the-group-stage/ |access-date=22 September 2023 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=5 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231005100104/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2023/09/22/they-didn-t-make-it-at-the-opening-phase-of-the-group-stage/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2023 |title=Al-Kaabi is the top scorer in Olympiacos |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%AA%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%88%D8%B3-1236392.html |access-date=22 September 2023 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=22 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230922000127/https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%AA%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%88%D8%B3-1236392.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Six days later, El Kaabi went on to score another brace against [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris Thessaloniki]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 September 2023 |title=Olympiacos dominates Aris in "G. Karaiskakis" |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2023/09/27/olympiacos-dominates-aris-in-g-karaiskakis/ |access-date=4 October 2023 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=14 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231014210142/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2023/09/27/olympiacos-dominates-aris-in-g-karaiskakis/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League]], El Kaabi scored a goal in the first and second leg of the knockout round play-offs, thus qualifying them for the round of 16.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-15 |title=A "red-and-white" lead to qualification |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/02/15/a-red-and-white-lead-to-qualification/ |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315102836/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/02/15/a-red-and-white-lead-to-qualification/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-22 |title=The Legend's Qualification in Budapest |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/02/23/the-legend-s-qualification-in-budapest/ |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315102835/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/02/23/the-legend-s-qualification-in-budapest/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the round of 16, Olympiacos faced [[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]], with El Kaabi scoring a goal in the first leg and a brace in the second, again qualifying them for the final 8.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-07 |title=Couldn't make it against Maccabi Tel Aviv |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/03/07/couldn-t-make-it-against-maccabi-tel-aviv/ |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315102837/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/03/07/couldn-t-make-it-against-maccabi-tel-aviv/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-15 |title=Legendary seals historical qualification in Serbia |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/03/15/legendary-seals-historical-qualification-in-serbia/ |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315131239/https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/03/15/legendary-seals-historical-qualification-in-serbia/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 2 May, El Kaabi scored a hat-trick in a 4–2 away win over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in the Europa Conference League semi-final first leg,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Ben |date=2024-05-02 |title=Aston Villa have mountain to climb after El Kaabi earns Olympiakos first-leg win |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/may/02/aston-villa-olympiakos-europa-conference-league-semi-final-first-leg-match-report |access-date=2025-04-25 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> the first ever hat-trick at the semifinal phase of Conference League.<ref name="UEFAKaabiscorer"/> A week later, on 9 May, he scored a brace in a 2–0 victory against Aston Villa in the second leg, sending his club to the [[2024 UEFA Europa Conference League final|Conference League final]], the first European final in their history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68978831 |title=Olympiakos 2–0 Aston Villa |publisher=BBC Sport |date=9 May 2024 |access-date=9 May 2024 |archive-date=9 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240509072246/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68978831 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Ben |date=2024-05-09 |title=El Kaabi's double crushes Aston Villa hopes of comeback at Olympiakos |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/may/09/olympiakos-aston-villa-europa-conference-league-semi-final-second-leg-match-report |access-date=2025-04-25 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He scored the only goal of the final in extra time as Olympiacos defeated [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] 1–0 to become the first Greek side to win a major European trophy.<ref name=UECLtitle>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/news/028d-1b01e5ec31a5-144c1f00e4f3-1000--olympiacos-1-0-fiorentina-aet-el-kaabi-swoops-to-secure-g/ |title=El Kaabi swoops to secure Greece's first major European trophy |publisher=UEFA |date=29 May 2024 |access-date=30 May 2024 |archive-date=30 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530003227/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaconferenceleague/news/028d-1b01e5ec31a5-144c1f00e4f3-1000--olympiacos-1-0-fiorentina-aet-el-kaabi-swoops-to-secure-g/ |url-status=live }}</ref> El Kaabi scored a total of 11 goals at the knockout phase, more than any other player during any single UEFA club competition, while the total of 14 goals during the group stage and knockout phases is a record for an African player.<ref name="UEFAKaabiscorer">{{cite web |title=2023/24 Europa Conference League top scorer: Ayoub El Kaabi |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/news/0285-1909e7690886-36b8a2ae5e09-1000--top-scorer-el-kaabi/ |website=[[UEFA]] |access-date=30 May 2024 |language=en |date=29 May 2024 |archive-date=29 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240529220611/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaconferenceleague/news/0285-1909e7690886-36b8a2ae5e09-1000--top-scorer-el-kaabi/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

During a match against [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK]] in the [[2024–25 Super League Greece]] play-offs, he scored the only goal of the game at 55 minutes. Olympiacos thus defeated AEK and were crowned champions.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-13 |title=48 και δεν είναι αρκετά: Ο Ολυμπιακός είναι πρωταθλητής Ελλάδας |trans-title=48 and it's not enough: Olympiacos is the Greek champion. |url=https://www.tovima.gr/2025/04/13/sports/olympiakos-aek-1-0-o-el-kaampi-ton-estepse-ksana-protathliti/ |access-date=2025-04-16 |website=ΤΟ ΒΗΜΑ |language=el}}</ref> On 17 May 2025, El Kaabi scored in the [[2025 Greek Football Cup final|final]] of the Greek Cup to defeat [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]] to help the club secure a domestic double.<ref name="GreekCupwin" />

