==International career==
El Kaabi made his international debut for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]] on 13 January 2018 in a [[2018 African Nations Championship#Group stage|2018 Africa Nations Championship group stage]] match against [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]], scoring two goals.<ref>{{cite news |language=en |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/01/238290/morocco-crushes-mauritania-4-0-opening-match-chan-2018/ |title=Morocco Crushes Mauritania 4-0 in Opening Match of CHAN 2018 |newspaper=Morocco World News |date=13 January 2018 |access-date=26 January 2018 |archive-date=27 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180127083835/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/01/238290/morocco-crushes-mauritania-4-0-opening-match-chan-2018/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 June 2018|title=Player to watch: Ayoub el Kaabi|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1414202|access-date=10 January 2022|website=DAWN.COM|language=en|archive-date=10 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220110112737/https://www.dawn.com/news/1414202|url-status=live}}</ref>

The footballer was named Man of The Match on 31 January after Morocco's match against Libya during CHAN's semi-final match. Morocco won the game 3-1.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ayoub El Kaabi brace sends Morocco into CHAN final - 2018 CHAN - Libya|url=https://africanfootball.com/news/741523/Ayoub-El-Kaabi-brace-sends-Morocco-into-CHAN-final|access-date=6 January 2022|website=African Football|archive-date=6 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220106204913/https://africanfootball.com/news/741523/Ayoub-El-Kaabi-brace-sends-Morocco-into-CHAN-final|url-status=live}}</ref> Morocco was set to face [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] in the finals. On 4 February 2018, Morocco defeated [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] 4–0, El Kaabi scored a goal in the 73rd minute of the match.<ref>{{Cite news|date=4 February 2018|title=El Kaabi hits ninth goal as Morocco whip Nigeria|url=https://t.guardian.ng/sport/el-kaabi-hits-ninth-goal-as-morocco-whip-nigeria/|location=Lagos, Nigeria|access-date=6 January 2022|newspaper=[[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]]|language=en-US}}{{Dead link|date=May 2024 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The Confederation of African Football (CAF) chose El Kaabi as the best player of the tournament, and he was top scorer with 9 goals in 5 matches.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=CAF-Confedération Africaine du Football|title=El Kaabi named Total man of the tournament|url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/el-kaabi-named-total-man-of-the-tournament|access-date=24 December 2021|website=CAFOnline.com|language=en|archive-date=24 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211224113537/https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/el-kaabi-named-total-man-of-the-tournament|url-status=live}}</ref> El Kaabi scored his first international [[hat trick]] for the [[Morocco A' national football team|local national team]] on 17 January 2018 against [[Guinea national football team|Guinea]].<ref>{{cite news |language=en |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/01/238564/chan-2018-morocco-beats-guinea-thanks-kaabis-hat-trick-ayoub-el-kaabi/ |title=CHAN: Morocco Beats Guinea Thanks to Kaabi's Hat-trick |newspaper=Morocco World News |date=17 January 2018 |access-date=26 January 2018 |archive-date=27 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180127004447/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/01/238564/chan-2018-morocco-beats-guinea-thanks-kaabis-hat-trick-ayoub-el-kaabi/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2018, he was named in Morocco's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Boufal left out of Morocco squad |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/amp/football/441603882018 }}{{dead link|date=September 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=13 March 2018|title=CHAN hero El Kaabi rewarded with Morocco call-up|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/morocco/story/3417894/chan-hero-ayoub-el-kaabi-rewarded-with-morocco-call-up|access-date=10 January 2022|website=ESPN.com|language=en|archive-date=10 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220110223453/https://www.espn.com/soccer/morocco/story/3417894/chan-hero-ayoub-el-kaabi-rewarded-with-morocco-call-up|url-status=live}}</ref> He played only 2 matches out of the 3 in the World Cup, played the first match as the starting 11 against [[Iran national football team|Iran]] and coming on the 69th minute as substitute for [[Khalid Boutaib]] against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]. El Kaabi represented Morocco in the [[2020 African Nations Championship]], scoring a total of three goals which helped his country to achieve the title and becoming the first and only country to win the Championship back to back.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=CAF-Confedération Africaine du Football|title=Morocco win second CHAN title after defeating Mali in final|url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/morocco-win-second-chan-title-after-defeating-mali-in-final|access-date=24 November 2021|website=CAFOnline.com|language=en|archive-date=24 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124202824/https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/morocco-win-second-chan-title-after-defeating-mali-in-final|url-status=live}}</ref> His most appreciated goal is the goal he scored in the final against [[Mali national football team|Mali]] in the 79th minute that guaranteed them the win.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mali vs Morocco|url=https://www.fotmob.com/match/3284401/matchfacts/mali-vs-morocco|access-date=10 January 2022|website=FotMob|language=en|archive-date=10 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220110105907/https://www.fotmob.com/match/3284401/matchfacts/mali-vs-morocco|url-status=live}}</ref> After his performances with the Moroccan A' for two years achieving two African titles, the coach of the main Morocco national team, [[Vahid Halilhodžić]], was impressed and decided to call him up to represent Morocco in [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2022 World Cup qualifiers]]. In his first six matches with the team, he managed to score five goals.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2022 World Cup Qualifiers: Morocco thrash diarrhoea-hit Guinea-Bissau as Sudan hold Guinea {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/en-ug/news/2022-world-cup-qualifiers-morocco-thrash-diarrhoea-hit/86g4u3escmuw1qmkmjvjfibri|access-date=24 November 2021|website=www.goal.com|archive-date=24 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124203749/https://www.goal.com/en-ug/news/2022-world-cup-qualifiers-morocco-thrash-diarrhoea-hit/86g4u3escmuw1qmkmjvjfibri|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Senegal and Morocco reach World Cup play-offs|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/58877606|access-date=24 November 2021|archive-date=24 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124203753/https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/58877606|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Twenty-one nations vie for eight berths in Africa|url=https://www.fifa.com/news/origin1904-p.cxm.fifa.comafrica-november-2021-world-cup-qualifying-preview|access-date=24 November 2021|website=www.fifa.com|language=en}}</ref> On 28 December 2023, he was named in the 27-man squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] in Ivory Coast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lematin.ma/sports/la-liste-des-27-joueurs-de-walid-regragui-pour-la-can-2023/206721|title=Lions de l'Atlas : La liste des 27 joueurs de Walid Regragui pour la CAN 2023|publisher=[[Le Matin (Morocco)|Le Matin]]|first=Youssef|last=Moutmaine|date=28 December 2023|access-date=28 December 2023|language=fr|archive-date=8 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240108134328/https://lematin.ma/sports/la-liste-des-27-joueurs-de-walid-regragui-pour-la-can-2023/206721|url-status=live}}</ref> On 11 June 2024, El Kaabi scored his first hat-trick for the national team in a 6–0 victory against [[Congo national football team|Congo]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2026 World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-06-11 |title=Morocco beat Congo Brazzaville 6-0 in WC African Qualifiers |url=https://en.hespress.com/86520-morocco-beat-congo-brazzaville-6-0-in-wc-african-qualifiers.html |access-date=2024-06-11 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Grand close to Match Day 03 and 04 of FIFA World Cup qualifiers |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/grand-close-to-match-day-03-and-04-of-fifa-world-cup-qualifiers/ |access-date=2024-06-11 |website=Grand close to Match Day 03 and 04 of FIFA World Cup qualifiers |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, El Kaabi was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

On 17 March 2026, El Kaabi’s Morocco were crowned AFCON winners after CAF overturned Senegal’s result and awarded a 3‑0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-17 |title=Afcon 2025: Morocco declared the winners after CAF overturns final defeat to Senegal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ce949glzzglo |access-date=2026-03-17 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Playing style==
A competition ambassador at the 2018 African Nations Championship, [[Adel Chedli]], described El Kaabi as reminiscent of [[Didier Drogba]], [[Samuel Eto'o]] and [[Florent Malouda]].<ref>{{cite web |date=3 February 2018 |title=Ayoub El Kaabi, la comète qui embrase le football marocain |trans-title=Ayoub El Kaabi, the comet that ignites Moroccan football. |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20180203-ayoub-el-kaabi-comete-embrase-le-football-marocain |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202065158/http://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20180203-ayoub-el-kaabi-comete-embrase-le-football-marocain |archive-date=2 February 2020 |access-date=22 July 2019 |publisher=Radio France Internationale |language=fr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
El Kaabi married his wife, Chaimae, in a traditional ceremony in Casablanca on 26 November 2018. The wedding was attended by family, friends, and notable figures from the football community.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ayoub El Kaabi's Marriage |url=https://www.bladi.net/mariage-ayoub-el-kaabi,53632.html |access-date=20 May 2024 |website=Bladi.net |archive-date=20 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240520130945/https://www.bladi.net/mariage-ayoub-el-kaabi,53632.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 9 September 2023, El Kaabi, along with his [[Morocco national football team|national teammates]], donated blood to those injured in the [[2023 Marrakesh-Safi earthquake]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 September 2023 |title="أسود الأطلس" يتبرعون بالدم في أكادير |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%A3%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%B3-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%B9%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%85-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%B1-1229384.html |access-date=9 September 2023 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=10 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230910134936/https://www.hespress.com/%d8%a3%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a3%d8%b7%d9%84%d8%b3-%d9%8a%d8%aa%d8%a8%d8%b1%d8%b9%d9%88%d9%86-%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%85-%d9%81%d9%8a-%d8%a3%d9%83%d8%a7%d8%af%d9%8a%d8%b1-1229384.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title="أسود الأطلس" يتبرعون بالدم.. عالم الرياضة يتضامن مع المغرب بعد الزلزال المدمر |trans-title="The Atlas Lions" donate blood... The sports world shows solidarity with Morocco after the devastating earthquake. |url=https://www.aljazeera.net/sport/2023/9/9/%d8%a3%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a3%d8%b7%d9%84%d8%b3-%d9%8a%d8%aa%d8%a8%d8%b1%d8%b9%d9%88%d9%86-%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%85-%d8%b9%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230911092914/https://www.aljazeera.net/sport/2023/9/9/%d8%a3%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a3%d8%b7%d9%84%d8%b3-%d9%8a%d8%aa%d8%a8%d8%b1%d8%b9%d9%88%d9%86-%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%85-%d8%b9%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85 |archive-date=11 September 2023 |access-date=9 September 2023 |website=www.aljazeera.net |language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=قطبي |first=ماجدة |date=9 September 2023 |title=زلزال الحوز.. الركراكي و"أسود الأطلس" يتبرعون بالدم |url=https://machahid24.com/sport/400897.html |access-date=9 September 2023 |website=مشاهد 24 |language=ar |archive-date=18 September 2023 |